Task: Design a small dashboard for model benchmarks.
Context: The dashboard should allow filtering by provider and display failure states.
Constraints: Include 3 filters (provider), show pass/fail status, use a bar chart for visualization, keep the design simple, total dashboard height ≤ 500px.
Output format:
```json
{
"dashboard": {
"title": "Model Benchmarks",
"filters": [
{"label": "Provider A", "type": "select"},
{"label": "Provider B", "type": "select"},
{"label": "Provider C", "type": "select"}
],
"chart": {
"type": "bar",
"data": {
"labels": ["Pass", "Fail"],
"datasets": [
{
"label": "Benchmarks",
"data": [0, 0]
}
]
}
},
"description": "A simple dashboard to visualize model benchmark results with provider filters and failure states."
}
}
```

